Undeads are the new factors of PVU that were introduced with the released of v3.1. To possess an Undead, you first need to hatch if from the Eggs (which can be found in the Minigames of Gathering Mode).

For now, the main use of the Undeads is to convert your LE into PVU Tokens through a feature called “Expedition”. Each Undead has its own stats and parameters, which encourages the users to possess and try as many different types of Undead as possible.

The Expedition trip takes at least 4 hours to convert your LE into 1 PVU, that means an Undead can only be deployed into Expedition for a duration with the multiple of 4 (example: 12 hours for 3 PVU Tokens)
Each Undead has its own capability of carrying a certain amount of LE, so be wise and deploy them in turns for the best profit.
When the Expedition trip is finished, you can claim back the PVU Tokens (via website) and in some case, the Undead might also bring back unexpected rewards from its arduous journey.

If, by a special reason that you need your Undead back at its Barn, you can prematurely Recall it back – but doing so will cost you some LE as a hasty retreat would likely cause you to lose something in the panic.
Each Undead has its own Fatigue bar, which is reduced the longer you send it into an Expedition trip.

The Fatigue will restore overtime when the Undead is not engaged in an Expedition trip, or you can spend LE to Nuture it to replenish its Fatigue faster. Be warned that the use of Nuture is not designed in a spammable manner, as the LE cost will increase with each use.
An Undead with the Fatigue of 49% or lower can’t be sent into Expedition – and also, you can’t send it into a trip that is longer than its Fatigue capability allows.

After being hatched from the Eggs, all the Undeads are in their juvenile stages. During this stage, they can’t be sent into combat and their only duties are to eat, sleep, grow and transmute LE into PVU Tokens.

By feeding the Undeads with various types of food, you can raise their Affection Level up. Higher Affection Level means better stats overall, resulting in higher amount of PVU Tokens converted, longer Expedition time, faster Fatigue regeneration rate... and even better chance to earn special rewards!

When an Undead reaches maximum Affection Level, it can be placed on the NFT Market and sold to other users. Be warned that switching the ownership between users resulting into reset in Affection Level. Love has to be mutually built up from the ground, no?
Each Undead has its own life circle – counting by days since the date it was born. For some mysterious reasons, this life circle seems to be halted when the Undeads are going on Expedition.
The life circle clock starts to tick again when the Undeads return to their Barn and resting, and can you guess what happened when the life circle ends?
Well… the Undead will be gone for good. But don’t weep yet, as it might leave something interesting back as a memento. Be sure to clean the Barn after an Undead has gone to check for any leftovers.

Don’t want to have such a hard time sending it off naturally? Well, you can also put an Undead with maximum Affection Level on the NFT Market. Also for some unknown reasons, time seems to be stopped here so it might be a wise decision to sell your Undeads to other users and get back some shiny Tokens for later use.

And don’t worry, since upon switching the ownership, an Undead doesn’t only reset ifs Affection Level, but so does its life circle! You can always pay a visit to it via the new owner’s Barn, but we can’t guaranteed that it would still remember you…

The Undead needs 48 hours to level up, even if it has accumulated enough EXP.
